IN	1 pound ground pork
IN	1 lemongrass stalk, bottom 5 inches only, smashed with rolling pin, then minced
IN	1/4 cup chopped shallots
IN	2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro
IN	2 tablespoons fish sauce (such as nam pla or nuoc nam)
IN	2 garlic cloves, chopped
IN	1 tablespoon vegetable oil
IN	1 teaspoon sugar
IN	1/2 teaspoon ground white pepper
IN	1 lemongrass stalk
IN	1/4 cup fresh lime juice
IN	1/4 cup fish sauce
IN	2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro
IN	2 tablespoons coarsely grated carrot
IN	4 teaspoons (packed) golden brown sugar
IN	2 teaspoons minced green Thai chile or serrano chile with seeds
IN	2 tablespoons vegetable oil
IN	1 head of butter lettuce, leaves separated
IN	1 small persian cucumber, thinly sliced
OT	Ingredient info: Fish sauce can be found in the Asian foods section of many supermarkets.
OT	For meatballs:
PR	Chill pork in freezer while making lemongrass paste. Combine lemongrass, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and remaining ingredients in processor; pulse until paste forms. Add chilled pork; pulse to blend. Shape into 24 balls (each about 1 tablespoonful). Place on rimmed baking sheet. Cover; chill at least 1 hour and up to 1 day.
OT	For dipping sauce and assembly:
PR	Cut bottom 3 inches from lemongrass. Smash with rolling pin, then mince. Measure 1 tablespoon and place in small bowl (reserve the rest for another use). Add lime juice, fish sauce, cilantro, carrot, sugar, and chile to bowl; whisk until sugar dissolves.
PR	Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat. Add meatballs; brown until cooked through, turning occasionally, about 15 minutes. Transfer to 1 side of large platter.
PR	Arrange lettuce leaves and cucumber on platter with meatballs. Allow guests to place meatballs in leaves, garnish with cucumber, and drizzle dipping sauce over.
